# AGENTS.md

This repository follows the TLB UI Standards. The canonical version lives in the `tlb-ui-standards` repository. This file is the in-repo copy that AI coding agents must read before producing UI code.

If you are an AI agent (Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, v0, Cline, or any MCP-aware tool) working in this repository, treat this file as authoritative.

## Stack You Are Allowed to Use

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| UI components | shadcn/ui in `src/components/ui/` |
| Primitives | @radix-ui/react-* (transitive via shadcn) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 with tokens in `src/styles/tailwind.css` |
| Class merging | `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts` |
| Icons | lucide-react |
| Charts | recharts |
| Forms | react-hook-form plus zod |
| Tables | @tanstack/react-table plus shadcn Table |
| State (local) | React state |
| State (cross-route) | zustand |
| Routing | react-router v7 |
| Auth | @azure/msal-react |
| Date / time | `Intl.DateTimeFormat` or `date-fns` |

## Forbidden Libraries

MUI, Ant Design, Chakra, Mantine, HeroUI, Fluent UI, Bootstrap, Heroicons, Font Awesome, Material Icons, Tabler, Phosphor, Emotion, styled-components, stitches, UnoCSS, Panda, vanilla-extract, moment.js, Chart.js, ApexCharts, Highcharts, Visx, Plotly, Nivo.

Adding any of these requires written Administrator approval. If you believe a task requires one of them, stop and ask the human.

## Hard Rules

1. Use shadcn primitives from `src/components/ui/`. When a primitive is missing, run `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` rather than re-implementing.
2. No inline hex, rgb, hsl, or named colors in JSX or CSS outside the `@theme` block in `src/styles/tailwind.css`.
3. Wrap every conditional className with `cn()`.
4. Define variants with `class-variance-authority` (`cva`).
5. Every interactive element has a discernible name. Every form input has a Label.
6. No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow.
7. No `style={{}}` for layout, spacing, color, or typography.
8. No em dashes. Use commas, periods, colons, or parentheses.

## Folder Conventions

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/            shadcn primitives
│   ├── layout/        AppShell, Sidebar, TopBar, PageHeader
│   ├── forms/         form composites
│   ├── data/          DataTable, EmptyState, KpiTile, ChartCard
│   └── feature/<name>/  feature-specific
├── lib/
│   ├── utils.ts       cn()
│   └── ...
├── hooks/             one per file, prefix `use-`
├── schemas/           zod schemas, one per resource
├── styles/
│   └── tailwind.css   tokens via @theme
└── routes/ or pages/  route components only
```

## Color and Typography (Quick Reference)

- Primary: `bg-primary text-primary-foreground` (TLB Orange on white).
- Destructive: `bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground` (TLB Dark Orange).
- Body: `text-foreground` on `bg-background`.
- Display headings: `font-display uppercase tracking-tight`.
- Body: `font-sans` (Helvetica, Arial).

## Copy Rules

- Plain-spoken and active voice. Short.
- Title case for primary actions and section headers. Sentence case for help text.
- "Client" not "customer." "Firm" not "company." "Founder" not "owner."
- No "leverage" as a verb. No "synergy", "best-in-class", "world-class", "cutting-edge".
- No filler openers (basically, frankly, honestly).
- No em dashes anywhere.

## Before You Submit

1. `npm run lint` and `npm run typecheck` pass.
2. Light and dark mode both render correctly.
3. Keyboard navigation works end to end with visible focus.
4. Every interactive element has a discernible name.
5. Every form input has a Label.
6. No new dependencies, or new dependencies justified and on the approved list.

## When You Are Stuck

Stop and ask the human. Do not invent a pattern. Do not add a library. Do not silently violate any rule to make the task easier.
